"n.大批离去，成群外出 【英】 n.大批离去，成群外 出(a mass departure or emigration) 【考】 反义词：influx(流入 ) 【例】 The refugee made an exodus to a safe place. n. 大批离去 【源】圣经?旧约中《出埃及记》原指: 以色列人离开埃及ex出, odus路－顺着大路出去－大批离去 【记】ex出, dus = bus: 座大巴出去－成批离去ex出, us我们: 我们出去－成批离去 【反】influx(n 流入) 【记】ex 出 + odo, 源自 road 路 →沿着路外出；road 去掉r 就是od；ex + outdore 出门 【相关】odometer 里程表 Exodus  late Old English, the second book of the Old Testament, from Latin exodus, from Greek exodos ""a military expedition; a solemn procession; departure; death,"" literally ""a going out,"" from ex- ""out"" (see ex-) + hodos ""way"" (see cede). General sense (with lower-case -e-) is from 1620s."
